## Before modifying ANY file, check `/docs/protected-boundaries.md`

### If the file is рџ”ґ Critical

1. **STOP.** Do NOT modify.
2. Output the full proposed diff.
3. List every feature and file that imports or depends on this file (use the Dependency Map in `/docs/protected-boundaries.md`).
4. Wait for explicit human approval before applying.

рџ”ґ Critical files (quick reference вЂ” see `/docs/protected-boundaries.md` for full details):

- `src/app/App.tsx` вЂ” global state owner, `VpnStatus` type
- `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` вЂ” `MapLayerOption`, `VpnFeatureType` types
- `src/app/components/layerData.ts` вЂ” layer tier system (3 features depend on it)
- `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx` вЂ” flag utilities (5 files depend on it)
- `src/app/components/ui/utils.ts` вЂ” `cn()` utility (~43 shadcn files depend on it)
- `src/styles/theme.css` вЂ” CSS tokens for entire app
- `src/styles/tailwind.css` вЂ” Tailwind v4 entry
- `src/styles/fonts.css` вЂ” font stack aliases
- `src/styles/index.css` вЂ” master CSS import chain
- `vite.config.ts` вЂ” build configuration
- `index.html` вЂ” SPA entry
- `package.json` вЂ” dependencies and scripts

### If the file is рџџЎ Cautious

1. Check the **"Safe Changes"** column in `/docs/protected-boundaries.md` вЂ” if your change qualifies (e.g. adding a new country entry to `countryData.ts` following existing shape), proceed.
2. If your change falls under **"Unsafe Changes"** (e.g. changing `CountryData` interface fields, renaming exports, altering props), treat it as рџ”ґ Critical: stop, output diff, list dependents, wait for approval.
3. After any modification to a рџџЎ file, output: `вљ пёЏ Modified cautious file [path] вЂ” [what changed] вЂ” affects: [list features]`

рџџЎ Cautious files (quick reference):

- `src/app/components/countryData.ts`
- `src/app/components/ISPRegulationsPanel.tsx`
- `src/app/components/CountryBrowser.tsx`
